Awesome!
Really cool to see. Go half hour earlier and walk the bridge to the other side and see the views over the river. Da Nang is beautifully vibrant at night and lit up so well it‚Äôs stunning. There are places for coffee or drinks nearby however it gets so crazy busy. Everyone is happy and great but wildly over crowded. Not to let this deter you but just to be prepared. There‚Äôs a night market right nearby which people come from and then go to after the Dragon Bridge show. If you stand on the bridge or underneath on either side you can get soaked. Otherwise there is a huge standing area a bit further down the street that is a perfect viewing point without getting wet. Would recommend for the light show and if you have kids. The show lasts about 10 minutes in total. Started with fire then ends with water.
Visited March 2023
