I SUPPOSE IF YOU'RE IN DA NANG, YOU HAVE TO GO AND SEE IT...
Mar 2020 ‚Ä¢ Family
Having only been in Da Nang an hour or so, we decided to make our way and see the Saturday night show at the dragon bridge which, I believe, starts at 21.00.
We walked and found ourselves outside a riverside entertainment centre, which had sumptuous 'pints' of draught Tiger (@30,000 ƒë·ªìng) and a superb view of the 'Dragon Bridge'.
However, we felt a touch underwhelmed by the actual 5 to 10 minute display, the very beginning being the best part when the dragon snorts out the first burst of fire.
This said, it's worth going to see, as the night market is right next door, and there's some interesting grub to be eaten, even though the stuff in the market are a bit mundane.
