Very disappointing
Feb 2020
We stayed at the SenRiver Hotel which is situate at the 'tail end' of the Dragon. The Dragon only breathes fire twice on Saturday and Sunday nights at 9.00pm. We were happily chatting away when the first blaze took place. We hadn't realised that it was 9 o'clock ! By the time we had set our camera's the second breathe had already happened and we didn't get a single shot !!
A couple of rockets launched just before the event would have alerted us to the time and prepared us. Two 5 second blasts of flame hardly warrant all the hype. Don't bother making a special effort to see it. It's not worth it
